  "title": "Pilgrim's Progress §169: Now, as Christian went on his way, he came to a little ascent, which was cast up on pur...",
  "body": "Now, as Christian went on his way, he came to a little ascent, which was cast up on purpose that pilgrims might see before them. Up there, therefore, Christian went, and looking forward, he saw Faithful before him, upon his journey. Then said Christian aloud, \"Ho! ho! So-ho! stay, and I will be your companion!\" At that, Faithful looked behind him; to whom Christian cried again, \"Stay, stay, till I come up to you!\" But Faithful answered, \"No, I am upon my life, and the avenger of blood is behind me.\"",
